# SQLite local/test databases + their sidecars (journal, WAL, SHM).
#
# phpunit.xml configures CI tests with DB_CONNECTION=sqlite + DB_DATABASE=:memory:
# so CI leaves no file behind. The file `server/budojo` only materialises when
# the local .env sets DB_DATABASE to a filesystem path for dev/tinker, or when
# PEST parallel workers shard the DB per worker (`budojo_test_1`, `budojo_test_2`,
# …).
#
# SQLite also writes `<db>-journal`, `<db>-wal`, `<db>-shm` alongside the DB
# file, so matching just the base name isn't enough — the `budojo-*` and the
# `*.sqlite-*` patterns cover both extension-less and extensioned DBs.
budojo
budojo-*
budojo_test_*
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-journal
*.sqlite-wal
*.sqlite-shm
